#Erstellung Pivot-Tabelle fr Nutzungsdauer des Kontos
grouped = credit.groupby('ID')
pivot_tb = credit.pivot(index = 'ID', columns = 'MONTHS_BALANCE', values = 'STATUS')
In [78]:
pivot_tb['Erffnung'] = grouped['MONTHS_BALANCE'].min() # Monat der Erffnung
pivot_tb['Schlieung'] = grouped['MONTHS_BALANCE'].max() # Monat der Schlieung
pivot_tb['ID'] = pivot_tb.index #Kontonummer als Index festlegen
pivot_tb = pivot_tb[['ID', 'Erffnung', 'Schlieung']]
In [79]:
#Nutzungsdauer / Beobachtungsfenster == Monat der Schlieung - Monat der Erffnung
pivot_tb['Dauer'] = pivot_tb['Schlieung'] - pivot_tb['Erffnung']
pivot_tb.reset_index(drop = True, inplace = True)

#Vintage Tabelle
vintage = credit.groupby(['Erffnung','month_on_book']).agg({'ID': ['count']}) 
vintage.reset_index(inplace = True)
vintage.columns = ['Erffnung','month_on_book','Summe'] 
vintage['berfllig'] = np.nan
vintage = vintage[['Erffnung','month_on_book','berfllig']]
vintage = pd.merge(vintage,Gesamtheit, on = ['Erffnung'], how = 'left')
In [87]:
# berflligkeit 60 Tage
for j in range(-60,1):
    ls = []
    for i in range(0,61):
        due = list(credit[(credit['Status'] == 1) & (credit['month_on_book'] == i) & (credit['Erffnung'] == j)]['ID'])
        ls.extend(due)
        vintage.loc[(vintage['month_on_book'] == i) & (vintage['Erffnung'] == j), 'berfllig'] = len(set(ls))
        
vintage['berflligkeit']  = vintage['berfllig'] / vintage['Summe'] # berflligkeit Rate

In [95]:
#Funktion calc_iy zur Berechnung von IV und WoE
#IV: Information Value
#WoE: Weight of Evidence
#Theoritische Grundlagen zur Berechnung des IV und WoE siehe Masterarbeit

def calc_iv(df, feature, target, pr=False):
    lst = []
    df[feature] = df[feature].fillna("NULL")

    for i in range(df[feature].nunique()):
        val = list(df[feature].unique())[i]
        lst.append([feature,                                                        # Merkmal
                    val,                                                            # Ausprgung
                    df[df[feature] == val].count()[feature],                        # Insgesamt
                    df[(df[feature] == val) & (df[target] == 0)].count()[feature],  # Gut (Risoko == Nein)
                    df[(df[feature] == val) & (df[target] == 1)].count()[feature]]) # Schlecht (Risoko == Ja)

    data = pd.DataFrame(lst, columns=['Merkmal', 'Ausprgung', 'Insgesamt', 'Gut', 'Schlecht'])
    data['Anteil'] = data['Insgesamt'] / data['Insgesamt'].sum()
    data['davon "schlecht"'] = data['Schlecht'] / data['Insgesamt']
    data['Verteilung "gut"'] = (data['Insgesamt'] - data['Schlecht']) / (data['Insgesamt'].sum() - data['Schlecht'].sum())
    data['Verteilung "schlecht"'] = data['Schlecht'] / data['Schlecht'].sum()
    data['WoE'] = np.log(data['Verteilung "gut"'] / data['Verteilung "schlecht"'])
    
    data = data.replace({'WoE': {np.inf: 0, -np.inf: 0}})

    data['IV'] = data['WoE'] * (data['Verteilung "gut"'] - data['Verteilung "schlecht"'])

    data = data.sort_values(by=['Merkmal', 'Ausprgung'], ascending=[True, True])
    data.index = range(len(data.index))

    if pr:
        print(data)
        print('IV = ', data['IV'].sum())

    iv = data['IV'].sum()
    print('IV dises Merkmals ist:',iv)
    print(df[feature].value_counts())
    return iv, data
In [96]:
#Funktion zur Aktualisierung des IV in der Tabelle

def convert_dummy(df, feature,rank=0):
    pos = pd.get_dummies(df[feature], prefix=feature)
    mode = df[feature].value_counts().index[rank]
    biggest = feature + '_' + str(mode)
    pos.drop([biggest],axis=1,inplace=True)
    df.drop([feature],axis=1,inplace=True)
    df=df.join(pos)
    return df
In [97]:
#Funktion zur Einteilung der kontinuierlichen Merkmale in kategorischen Merkmale
def get_category(df, col, binsnum, labels, qcut = False):
    if qcut:
        localdf = pd.qcut(df[col], q = binsnum, labels = labels)
    else:
        localdf = pd.cut(df[col], bins = binsnum, labels = labels)
        
    localdf = pd.DataFrame(localdf)
    name = 'gp' + '_' + col
    localdf[name] = localdf[col]
    df = df.join(localdf[name])
    df[name] = df[name].astype(object)
    return df
In [98]:
def plot_confusion_matrix(cm, classes,
                          normalize=False,
                          title='Confusion matrix',
                          cmap=plt.cm.Blues):
    if normalize:
        cm = cm.astype('float') / cm.sum(axis=1)[:, np.newaxis]
        
    print(cm)

    plt.imshow(cm, interpolation='nearest', cmap=cmap)
    plt.title(title)
    plt.colorbar()
    tick_marks = np.arange(len(classes))
    plt.xticks(tick_marks, classes)
    plt.yticks(tick_marks, classes)

    fmt = '.2f' if normalize else 'd'
    thresh = cm.max() / 2.
    for i, j in itertools.product(range(cm.shape[0]), range(cm.shape[1])):
        plt.text(j, i, format(cm[i, j], fmt),
                 horizontalalignment="center",
                 color="white" if cm[i, j] > thresh else "black")

    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.ylabel('True label')
    plt.xlabel('Predicted label')

4.2 Optimierung des Entscheidungsbaums¶

4.2.1 GridSearchCV¶

4.2.1.1 Optimierung der maximalen Tiefe (max_depth)¶

In [136]:
# Definition der Paramerkombination
params = {"max_depth": range(1,40)}
#Suchraum: 1 bis 39 <-- Insgesamt 39 Merkmale

# Erstellen des Grids
grid = GridSearchCV(estimator=clf_base, param_grid=params,
                    cv=10, verbose=3, n_jobs=-1)

# Training des Grids
grid.fit(X_train, y_train)
print(grid.best_params_, grid.best_score_)

Fitting 10 folds for each of 39 candidates, totalling 390 fits
{'max_depth': 31} 0.960747623729044
In [137]:
# function for fitting trees of various depths on the training data using cross-validation
def run_cross_validation_on_trees(X, y, tree_depths, cv=10, scoring='accuracy'):
    cv_scores_list = []
    cv_scores_std = []
    cv_scores_mean = []
    accuracy_scores = []
    for depth in tree_depths:
        tree_model = DecisionTreeClassifier(max_depth=depth, random_state=576804)
        cv_scores = cross_val_score(tree_model, X, y, cv=cv, scoring=scoring)
        cv_scores_list.append(cv_scores)
        cv_scores_mean.append(cv_scores.mean())
        cv_scores_std.append(cv_scores.std())
        accuracy_scores.append(tree_model.fit(X, y).score(X, y))
    cv_scores_mean = np.array(cv_scores_mean)
    cv_scores_std = np.array(cv_scores_std)
    accuracy_scores = np.array(accuracy_scores)
    return cv_scores_mean, cv_scores_std, accuracy_scores
  
# function for plotting cross-validation results
def plot_cross_validation_on_trees(depths, cv_scores_mean, cv_scores_std, accuracy_scores, title):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(1,1, figsize=(15,5))
    ax.plot(depths, cv_scores_mean, '-o', label='Genauigkeit der Kreuzvalidierung', alpha=0.9)
    ax.fill_between(depths, cv_scores_mean-2*cv_scores_std, cv_scores_mean+2*cv_scores_std, alpha=0.2)
    ylim = plt.ylim()
    ax.plot(depths, accuracy_scores, '-*', label='Genauigkeit des Trainings', alpha=0.9)
    ax.set_title(title, fontsize=16)
    ax.set_xlabel('Tiefe des Baumes', fontsize=14)
    ax.set_ylabel('Genauigkeit', fontsize=14)
    ax.set_ylim(ylim)
    ax.set_xticks(depths)
    ax.legend()

sm_tree_depths = range(1,40)
sm_cv_scores_mean, sm_cv_scores_std, sm_accuracy_scores = run_cross_validation_on_trees(X_train, y_train, sm_tree_depths)


plot_cross_validation_on_trees(sm_tree_depths, sm_cv_scores_mean, sm_cv_scores_std, sm_accuracy_scores, 
                               'Genauigkeit nach Tiefe des Entscheidungsbaums mit Trainingsdaten')

idx_max = sm_cv_scores_mean.argmax()
sm_best_tree_depth = sm_tree_depths[idx_max]
sm_best_tree_cv_score = sm_cv_scores_mean[idx_max]
sm_best_tree_cv_score_std = sm_cv_scores_std[idx_max]
print('The depth-{} tree achieves the best mean cross-validation accuracy {} +/- {}% on training dataset'.format(
      sm_best_tree_depth, round(sm_best_tree_cv_score*100,5), round(sm_best_tree_cv_score_std*100, 5)))

The depth-31 tree achieves the best mean cross-validation accuracy 96.07476 +/- 0.24799% on training dataset

4.2.1.2 Optimierung der Kombination der Hyperparameter¶

In [138]:
# Definition der Paramerkombination
params = {"criterion": ["gini", "entropy"],
          "max_depth":range(30,40),
         "min_samples_split": range(1,6),
         "min_samples_leaf": range(1,6)}

# Erstellen des Grids
grid = GridSearchCV(estimator=clf_base, param_grid=params,
                    cv=10, verbose=3, n_jobs=-1)

# Training des Grids
grid.fit(X_train, y_train)
print(grid.best_params_, grid.best_score_)

mit GirdSearchCV optimiertes Modell¶

clf_grid_opt = DecisionTreeClassifier(criterion='entropy',
                             max_depth=33,

mit GirdSearchCV optimiertes Modell (max_depth = 8)¶

# Definition der Paramerkombination
params = {"max_depth": range(8,9), 
         "criterion": ["gini", "entropy"],
         "min_samples_split": range(1,5),
         "min_samples_leaf": range(1,5),
         }

                    cv=10, verbose=3, n_jobs=-1)

# Training des Grids
grid.fit(X_train, y_train)
print(grid.best_params_, grid.best_score_)

         "min_samples_leaf": range(1,6)}

                               cv = 10, n_iter = 100, n_jobs=-1, random_state=576504)

In [158]:
def get_rules(tree, feature_names, class_names):
    tree_ = tree.tree_
    feature_name = [
        feature_names[i] if i != _tree.TREE_UNDEFINED else "undefined!"
        for i in tree_.feature
    ]

    paths = []
    path = []
    
    def recurse(node, path, paths):
        
        if tree_.feature[node] != _tree.TREE_UNDEFINED:
            name = feature_name[node]
            threshold = tree_.threshold[node]
            p1, p2 = list(path), list(path)
            p1 += [f"({name} <= {np.round(threshold, 3)})"]
            recurse(tree_.children_left[node], p1, paths)
            p2 += [f"({name} > {np.round(threshold, 3)})"]
            recurse(tree_.children_right[node], p2, paths)
        else:
            path += [(tree_.value[node], tree_.n_node_samples[node])]
            paths += [path]
            
    recurse(0, path, paths)

    # sort by samples count
    samples_count = [p[-1][1] for p in paths]
    ii = list(np.argsort(samples_count))
    paths = [paths[i] for i in reversed(ii)]
    
    rules = []
    for path in paths:
        rule = "if "
        
        for p in path[:-1]:
            if rule != "if ":
                rule += " and "
            rule += str(p)
        rule += " then "
        if class_names is None:
            rule += "response: "+str(np.round(path[-1][0][0][0],3))
        else:
            classes = path[-1][0][0]
            l = np.argmax(classes)
            rule += f"class: {class_names[l]} (proba: {np.round(100.0*classes[l]/np.sum(classes),2)}%)"
        rule += f" | based on {path[-1][1]:,} samples"
        rules += [rule]
        
    return rules

5.2 GOSDT-Modell¶

In [165]:
X = dataframe[dataframe.columns[:-1]]
y = dataframe[dataframe.columns[-1:]]

hyperparameters = {
    "regularization": 0,
    "time_limit": 3600,
    "verbose": True
}

model = GOSDT(hyperparameters)
model.fit(X, y)
# model.load("python/model/model.json")
# model.load("../gosdt_icml/model.json")
print("Execution Time: {}".format(model.time))

prediction = model.predict(X)
training_accuracy = model.score(X, y)
print("Training Accuracy: {}".format(training_accuracy))
print("Size: {}".format(model.leaves()))
print("Loss: {}".format(1 - training_accuracy))
print("Risk: {}".format(
    model.leaves() * hyperparameters["regularization"]
    + 1 - training_accuracy))
model.tree.__initialize_training_loss__(X, y)
print(model.tree)
print(model.latex())

In [171]:
def get_rules(tree, feature_names, class_names):
    tree_ = tree.tree_
    feature_name = [
        feature_names[i] if i != _tree.TREE_UNDEFINED else "undefined!"
        for i in tree_.feature
    ]

    paths = []
    path = []
    
    def recurse(node, path, paths):
        
        if tree_.feature[node] != _tree.TREE_UNDEFINED:
            name = feature_name[node]
            threshold = tree_.threshold[node]
            p1, p2 = list(path), list(path)
            p1 += [f"({name} <= {np.round(threshold, 3)})"]
            recurse(tree_.children_left[node], p1, paths)
            p2 += [f"({name} > {np.round(threshold, 3)})"]
            recurse(tree_.children_right[node], p2, paths)
        else:
            path += [(tree_.value[node], tree_.n_node_samples[node])]
            paths += [path]
            
    recurse(0, path, paths)

    # sort by samples count
    samples_count = [p[-1][1] for p in paths]
    ii = list(np.argsort(samples_count))
    paths = [paths[i] for i in reversed(ii)]
    
    rules = []
    for path in paths:
        rule = "if "
        
        for p in path[:-1]:
            if rule != "if ":
                rule += " and "
            rule += str(p)
        rule += " then "
        if class_names is None:
            rule += "response: "+str(np.round(path[-1][0][0][0],3))
        else:
            classes = path[-1][0][0]
            l = np.argmax(classes)
            rule += f"class: {class_names[l]} (proba: {np.round(100.0*classes[l]/np.sum(classes),2)}%)"
        rule += f" | based on {path[-1][1]:,} samples"
        rules += [rule]
        
    return rules

rules = get_rules(clf_5_opt, feature_names, target_names)
for r in rules:
    print(r)
